```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

df = pd.DataFrame({
    "sample": ["S1","S2","S3","S4","S5","S6","S7","S8"],
    "group":  ["G1","G1","G1","G2","G2","G2","G2","G2"],
    "score":  [80, 85, np.nan, 78, np.nan, 82, 90, np.nan]
})
```

```python
df['score_filled_global'] = df['score'].fillna(df['score'].mean())
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6,4))
color = np.where(df_diff['mean_score']> 0, 'blue', 'gray')
ax.bar(df_diff['group'], df_diff['mean_score'], color = color)
ax.set_title("Impact of Imputation Strategy")
ax.set_xlabel("Group")
ax.set_ylabel("Mean Score Difference")
ax.grid(False)
ax.axhline(y = 0, linestyle='--', linewidth=2, color = 'gray')
```
